<se_low>*: Oh! We don't often get travellers all the way out here. Are you on your way to the castle?
<se_low>*: Then you must've come from the castle?
<se_low>*: Then let me give you a piece of advice. There's no point in you going any further east to Ascantha Castle.
<se_low>*: Why? You'll soon see if you keep going. Anyway, I'd better get back to work.
<se_low>*: Really!? So the mourning is finally over!
<se_low>*: What wonderful news! Make sure you tell my wife, too. She'll be thrilled.
<se_low>*: I don't want to interfere, but you really shouldn't bother going to the castle. It'll be a wasted journey.
<se_high>*: Purr purr purrplexing!
<se_low>Morrie: You feeling a little lost, ay!? Then you should throw your eye over the memos I give you.
<se_low>Morrie: They have the monstrous informazione. Find them! Fight them! Send them to me!
<se_low>Morrie: It is not to worry, <nickname>. For you, it will be a slice of cake! I be awaiting!
<se_high>*: Meow.
<se_low>*: Ah, nice of you to drop in. Looks like you're keeping well.
<se_low>*: We're doing fine, thanks. My wife and I are thrilled to have Emma back.
<se_high>*: Meow meow!
<se_high>*: Mew.
<se_high>*: Purrr...
<se_low>*: Hello there! How good to see you looking so well!
<se_low>*: If you've come to see Emma, she's gone back to the castle.
<se_low>Morrie: When you have bring all the monsters to me, you come again and I show you a miracolo! You won't believe your eye!
<se_low>Morrie: You are a traveller, si, <nickname>? Don't let my monsters make you forget what you are doing, ay!?
<se_low>*: Ah, hello again. I haven't seen you in a while.
<se_low>*: Yes, I do have an occasional tussle with the odd monster or two, but if I don't work, we don't eat.
<se_low>*: If you go round the back of the house and follow the river downstream a while, you'll come to a path down to the embankment.
<se_low>*: Once you're down there, turn back on yourself and go upstream. They say there's some kind of cave up there.
<se_low>*: The people round these parts don't go there, mind. Once you go through the cave, you just come to a boring old hill with a nice view.
<se_low>*: Our granddaughter's coming home for the first time in two years. Dear Emma! I can't wait to see her.
<se_high>Marrie: Oh, I can't be goin' off gallivantin' as well now, can I? Who'd look after the place while Morrie's away...ay?

<se_high>Marrie: You know, he's a keen traveller, is Morrie.
Oh yeah, he won't have any trouble keepin' up with you all.
<se_high>Marrie: Hee hee, you know, it takes me back. We used to travel all over together. Gypsies, we were.
